Reactions to the 68th annual Golden Globe Awards
2011-01-17 02:11:10 GMT
Reactions to the 68th annual Golden Globe Awards, announced Sunday in Beverly Hills, Calif.:"I'm going to try to talk fast before that sad music comes on." — Steve Buscemi, accepting the best actor in a TV series drama for his role on "Boardwalk Empire.""I think I just dropped my heart between Natalie Portman and Julianne Moore. So if anyone sees that, please give it back to me." — Chris Colfer accepting his best supporting actor winner award for his role on the TV series "Glee.""It's going to be a night of partying and heavy drinking. Or as Charlie Sheen calls it — breakfast." — Host Ricky Gervais in his opening monologue.(Agencies)
